# FixOps — Agentic Ops North Star (consolidated spec)

This file merges **`agentic-ops-system.mdc`** (if present), **`context/comparison/GOAL.md`**, **`context/comparison/DECISIONS.md`**, and the **HTML vision pack** under `context/comparison/*.html` into one handoff document. **Authoritative AD entries** live in **DECISIONS.md**; this file is the **single checklist** for implementation.

**Scope:** describes **only the target programme** (what to build on a **new branch or new repo**). It is **not** tied to any prior codebase. Copy into a fresh repo as **requirements**.

---

## One-line principle

> **Inventory** tells the controller *how* to debug. **Dataflow** tells it *where* to start. **Workers** produce evidence in a **fixed contract**. The **controller** routes, stages context, and chains workers — **rules-first**. **LLM** assists extraction and narrative — **not** unbounded tool picking. **Evidence first**, conclusion second, **human approval before any mutating action**.

---

## What we are building

- **Alerts** and **general / ad-hoc operational queries** on the **same** LangGraph pipeline (bounded intent — **AD-013**); architecture does not fork.
- **Staged, budgeted** investigations with an **auditable decision log**.
- **Read-only default**; mutating actions only after approval (**AD-003**).

**North-star test (GOAL):** If an on-call reads the output **without opening a dashboard**, do they know **what broke, why, what to do, and what was ruled out**?

---

## Fixed architecture

| Topic | Decision |
|-------|-----------|
| **Topology** | **One controller**, **many workers**. Workers **do not** call each other; all fan-out through the **controller** with compact payloads. |
| **Deployment** | **Standalone workers** (separate processes / images), **HTTP + shared wire schema** (Pydantic/OpenAPI contract). Controller holds **URLs + timeouts** — **no** importing worker implementation packages. |
| **Routing** | **Rules-first**. LLM **extracts** entities → **deterministic routing table** picks the worker. LLM does **not** choose the next cluster/tool hop (**AD-002**). |
| **Execution** | **Human-gated** for mutations: suggest → approve → execute → verify. Auto-remediation **opt-in** for lower env only (**AD-003**). |
| **Metadata** | **Inventory** + **Dataflow graph** (**AD-004**). |
| **Context** | **Staged + budgeted** (**AD-005**): cheap → logs/metrics → code/runbooks/RAG when needed. Hard caps on workers, tool calls, tokens. |
| **Worker output** | **AD-006** JSON: `checked`, `findings`, `evidence_refs`, `ruled_out`, `confidence`, `next_suggested_check`. No raw log dumps between workers. |
| **Infra / tool access** | **AD-007** — mockable interfaces. **MCP-first** where it helps; **typed in-process adapters** (SDK/httpx) allowed per integration when MCP adds no clear win. |
| **Controller** | **LangGraph** (**AD-014**): checkpoints, conditional edges, human-in-the-loop. |
| **LLM** | **Shared external API** for controller + workers (**L2**); AD-006 governs wire format to controller. |
| **Confidence** | **AD-008** numeric gates — not “LLM says stop.” |
| **Institutional knowledge** | **AD-009** — RAG or equivalent (vector, hybrid, or vector-less retrieval); may ship **v1** with the rest of the stack. |
| **Inventory storage** | YAML in Git → validated load into **Postgres or Mongo** (**AD-010**). |
| **Credentials** | **AD-012** — controller **refs only**; workers **resolve** via pluggable backends (config → K8s secrets / AWS SM / Vault / …). Nothing sensitive in LLM context. |
| **MCP / adapters** | **AD-011** — community or custom MCP; reuse patterns from mature OSS (e.g. HolmesGPT toolsets, IncidentFox skills) **behind your interfaces**, not their orchestration model. |

**Workers do the reasoning** *inside* their boundary (which tools/adapters to call); the **controller** owns **cross-worker orchestration** and **rules-based** next steps.

---

## Intended workers

| Worker | Role |
|--------|------|
| **K8s / Infra** | Pods, deploys, events, logs |
| **Observability** | Prometheus / Loki / Tempo / Grafana |
| **Pipeline** | Airflow, Kafka, … |
| **App RCA** | Code, config |
| **DB** | Mongo / RDS |
| **Remediation planner** | Options (read-heavy) |
| **Executor** | **Approved** actions only |

---

## Routing table (illustrative)

- **Pod / deployment / namespace** → Infra worker (often no graph hop).
- **Service / DAG name** → Inventory → runtime → worker.
- **Collection / topic** → **Graph first** → owner → Inventory → worker.
- **Unclear entity** → labels / tags / history (when built).

---

## Standalone agents

- Deployable units; **HTTP** investigate endpoint; **AD-006** response.
- **MCP and/or adapters** inside worker; **shared LLM** optional for interpretation.
- Controller sends **inventory references** only for secrets.

---

## Implementation locks (2026-04-23)

| # | Lock |
|---|------|
| L1 | MCP-first + adapters per **AD-011** / **AD-007** |
| L2 | Shared LLM + AD-006 wire format |
| L3 | LangGraph (**AD-014**) |
| L4 | Thin inventory early; auto-sync later |
| L5 | Custom MCP for Airflow-style APIs when needed |
| L6 | Pluggable credential backends (**AD-012**) |
| L7 | Alerts + queries one pipeline (**AD-013**) |

